Cube-sphere grid illustration with interactive widgets 

Use the Plotly python API to directly show the 3D interactive graphics on the web page (convert python codes to javascript).

=== Code structure ==

---modules to be imported---
CubeSphere_math.py: 
- Do all the math (spherical geometry)
- Generate data that can be fed to Plotly graphic methods 
- This module itself is independent to any plotting methods

Plotly_layout.py:
- Set Plotly basic layout (background,title...)

---modules to run---
example1_step-by-step.py:
- An intuitive way to understand cube-sphere mesh generation

example2_compare-projections.py:
- 3 types of gnomonic grids in different colors

example3_stretch.py
- stretched cube-sphere for local mesh refinement 


